to the atmosphere

00:47:54.380 --> 00:47:56.335 align:middle line:90%
for about 3,000 years.

00:47:56.335 --> 00:48:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And somebody apparently built
a Stonehenge-like structure

00:48:00.330 --> 00:48:01.045 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:48:01.045 --> 00:48:02.170 align:middle line:90%
This hasn't been confirmed.

00:48:02.170 --> 00:48:02.785 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's fascinating.

00:48:02.785 --> 00:48:04.701 align:middle line:84%
>>CARLSON: Yeah, it
hasn't been confirmed yet.

00:48:04.701 --> 00:48:07.286 align:middle line:84%
I'm waiting to see what
subsequent research discloses.

00:48:07.286 --> 00:48:08.660 align:middle line:84%
But on one of the
stones, there's

00:48:08.660 --> 00:48:11.820 align:middle line:90%
what appears to be a mastodon.

00:48:11.820 --> 00:48:14.490 align:middle line:84%
Now, as far as I know, no
mastadons in North America

00:48:14.490 --> 00:48:18.420 align:middle line:84%
survived later than about
11,000 or 11,600 years ago.

00:48:18.420 --> 00:48:21.140 align:middle line:84%
So it could be just
a vestigial memory,

00:48:21.140 --> 00:48:25.510 align:middle line:84%
trying to preserve the
memory of the creatures.

00:48:25.510 --> 00:48:28.949 align:middle line:84%
There was some
traditions, and I've

00:48:28.949 --> 00:48:30.490 align:middle line:84%
